text: Per Fjästad (15 March 1883 - 18 October 1955) was a Swedish swimmer. He competed in the men's 200 metre breaststroke event at the 1908 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1883 births Category:1955 deaths Category:Swedish male swimmers Category:Olympic swimmers of Sweden Category:Swimmers at the 1908 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Stockholm
